{% comment %}
  section-hero — unified hero card for index / landing / tag pages.

  Replaces the bespoke treatments in _sass/_standards.scss and the inline
  block in _pages/20-quality-characteristics.md, and supplies a hero for
  /requirements/, /approaches/, and the tag pages.

  Section identity comes from the data-section attribute, which sets a
  CSS custom property --cat. The colour matches the home-directory rails,
  so the homepage acts as a legend for the destination section.

  Required:
    section  Color key. One of:
               qualities | requirements | approaches | standards | tag
    title    H1 text (plain).

  Optional:
    lede     Single paragraph of plain text shown below the title.
    meta     Inline metadata line (e.g. counts). HTML allowed.

  Example:
    {% raw %}{% include section-hero.liquid
        section="standards"
        title="Standards"
        lede="Authoritative references that ground qualities and requirements."
        meta="<b>184</b> standards across <b>13</b> categories." %}{% endraw %}

  Page-specific controls (chip rows, search inputs, A–Z bars) are placed
  in the consuming page after the include, not inside it — the hero stays
  a quiet identity card.
{% endcomment %}
<header class="section-hero" data-section="{{ include.section }}">
  <h1 class="section-hero__title">{{ include.title }}</h1>
  {% if include.lede %}<p class="section-hero__lede">{{ include.lede }}</p>{% endif %}
  {% if include.meta %}<p class="section-hero__meta">{{ include.meta }}</p>{% endif %}
</header>
